  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Integrated Protection and Life-Saving Health Services to Migrants and IDPs in Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Migration through Yemen has become a riskier process over the past 2-3 years and COVID-19 has exacerbated or accelerated certain trends. Migrants are amongst the most marginalized, excluded and vulnerable groups of people in need in Yemen. The on-going crisis and conflict, combined with the hardening attitudes of authorities against migrants, has increased their exposure to abuse and violence. As Yemen&#x2019;s humanitarian situation worsens, critical indicators such as access to health care, water and sanitation, food insecurity and malnutrition are worsening, and civilians are becoming increasingly exposed to conflict. This action aims to build on IOM and partners&apos; current migrant assistance and response capacity that meets the most critical needs of migrants traveling through Yemen. The action contributes to this goal through the continued employment of an integrated health and protection approach that prioritizes the most vulnerable migrants in Yemen at disembarkation points, along transit routes and hubs, and in locations where migrants are stranded or trapped as a result of conflict, crisis barriers and/or the impact of COVID-19 border closures. IOM and partners are providing migrants with access to health assistance, information on safe migration, individualized protection support and immediate short-term and emergency support that addresses demonstrated needs.</narrative>
  </description>
